<TITLE> Petrol pumps strike from Sunday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 08 (bdnews24.com)--- Owners' and workers' association of petrol pumps and tank-lorry unions have called an indefinite strike from Sunday 6am. Their 13-point demands include increasing the commission on fuel sales. But CNG filling stations will remain open during the strike. Muhammad Nazmul Haque, convener of the committee told bdnews24.com, "13 point demand has been given to the government." He said that the government had not taken any steps or initiatives in this regard till now. "All petrol pumps and tank-lorries will go on an indefinite strike." He said they had met the chairman of Bangladesh Petroleum Corporation on Thursday "But he could give us any decision either." Recently on Mar 14 the council called for a symbolic strike of six hours across the country. On Apr 12 the council declared to go on strike from May 09 if their demands are not met. Their demands include  increasing commission for fuel sale from 2 percent to 7 percent, implementation of policies for setting up petrol pumps, establish testing laboratory in every depot, accident insurance of Tk 500,000, building lorry terminal and rest-houses near the depots, increasing tank lorry charge and putting a stop to police harassment in the name of examining papers. There are nearly 9,000 petrol pumps across the country. bd
